Kenya’s first post-independence Attorney General, Sir Charles Njonjo, has now come out to dismiss reports of his death. Njonjo, in a statement to newsrooms on Sunday, termed the rumors as a great exaggeration. Njonjo, in the release, said he is alive and – matter of factly – enjoying his weekend at home. “Reports of my death have been greatly exaggerated. I am well and enjoying my weekend at home as we celebrate Utamaduni Day,” he said. Rumors of Njonjo’s death first hit the streets of social media on Saturday evening. Also Read: Video Of The Day: Former sports CS Hassan Wario convicted over Rio games scam